  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.5,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "- [David] What do you believe, wordsmiths,"
      },
      {
        "start": 3.2,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "and how does it help others?"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.1,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "What's your philosophy and\nhow does it benefit the world?"
      },
      {
        "start": 8.9,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "Those are the words\nwe're looking at today:"
      },
      {
        "start": 10.4,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "benefit and philosophy."
      },
      {
        "start": 12.3,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "I'll define these words, go\nthrough their word origins,"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.8,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "and then we'll use them in some sentences."
      },
      {
        "start": 16.8,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Let's start with benefit.\nIt's a noun and a verb."
      },
      {
        "start": 20.2,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "As a noun, it means an\nadvantage, something that helps,"
      },
      {
        "start": 23.5,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "and as a verb it has\nmuch the same meaning,"
      },
      {
        "start": 25.6,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "to get help or an\nadvantage from something."
      },
      {
        "start": 28.7,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "Benefits can also have to do with money."
      },
      {
        "start": 30.6,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "I work for Khan Academy\nand they pay me money"
      },
      {
        "start": 33.6,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "and give me vacation time"
      },
      {
        "start": 35.2,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "and health insurance and stuff like that."
      },
      {
        "start": 36.8,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Those are all benefits, perks of the job."
      },
      {
        "start": 40.1,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "Philosophy is a noun,"
      },
      {
        "start": 42.0,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "and it means a belief system"
      },
      {
        "start": 43.9,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "or a way of thinking about the world."
      },
      {
        "start": 46.2,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "If you're an optimist, you tend to believe"
      },
      {
        "start": 48.6,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "that things work out for the better."
      },
      {
        "start": 50.4,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "And if you're a pessimist,\nyou tend to believe"
      },
      {
        "start": 52.0,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "that things are bad and\nlikely to get worse."
      },
      {
        "start": 54.7,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "These two ways of thinking,\noptimism and pessimism,"
      },
      {
        "start": 57.8,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "are two different philosophies about life."
      },
      {
        "start": 61.1,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "A person who studies philosophy,\na philosopher, is someone"
      },
      {
        "start": 64.6,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "who thinks about the meaning\nof life, about belief systems."
      },
      {
        "start": 68.6,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "Let's break these words down."
      },
      {
        "start": 70.2,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "Benefit comes from the\nLatin bene, meaning good,"
      },
      {
        "start": 73.2,
        "duration": 4.5,
        "text": "and ultimately fit comes\nfrom fac, to make or to do."
      },
      {
        "start": 77.8,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "Related words include benefactor,"
      },
      {
        "start": 80.8,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "someone who gives money or support."
      },
      {
        "start": 82.6,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "So if you give money to Khan Academy,"
      },
      {
        "start": 84.5,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "you're one of our benefactors,\na person who does good."
      },
      {
        "start": 88.5,
        "duration": 3.7,
        "text": "Benevolent, kindly, nice, having goodwill,"
      },
      {
        "start": 92.2,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "that's what the vol part\nmeans is will or wishing."
      },
      {
        "start": 94.9,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "A benevolent person wants\ngood things to happen to you."
